cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with medical image super-resolution using generative adversarial networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method involves using a triplet loss function to improve the output image quality in a multistage model, which involves optimization and training of the network, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with medical imaging, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of generative adversarial networks involves optimization and training of the network, making it relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
